<br>
1.  the melee class was taunting/trying to gain aggro. In the case of an SK, sometimes we get overzealous with dots/procs etc...sorry. <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/smile.gif ALT=":)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END--> <br>
<br>
2.  The more likely case is proximity aggro.  Pets always stop closing on the mob they are targetting when they are within melee range.  They only move to stay within melee range. (Read-Max Melee Distance) PC's (especially tank-melee) tend to get as close to the mob as possible (Read-Min melee distance, or Ground Zero).   Try to keep any melees at max melee distance, or try to get your pets closer to the mob.  the objects closest to the mob generate the most hate. <p><!--EZCODE LINK START--><a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=292841"><!--EZCODE IMAGE START--><img src="http://users3.ev1.net/~cmusson/decsig56.jpg" style="border:0;"/><!--EZCODE IMAGE END--></a><!--EZCODE LINK END--></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#dcdeed><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub102.ezboard.com/bthemagicianstower.showUserPublicProfile?gid=izudin@themagicianstower>Izudin</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Conjurer</span><br>  Posts: 220<br> <font color=#333333>(12/3/02 3:22:36 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub102.ezboard.com/fthemagicianstowergeneral.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=8009.topic&index=43>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> <img src="http://www.ezboard.com/images/posticons/pi_lightbulb.gif" align=absmiddle>  Few more observations</span><hr size=1> Some more experiences from small pet groups, all happened in Velks while fighting spiders:<br>
<br>
Grouped with 59 mage, myself 60. Both of us were using GV: Air pet. His pet got hit 90% of the time. Positioning didnt help, it seems that the level determined the pet getting hit. Would have been interesting to see if I could have used GV: Water tho, but I didnt think of that.<br>
<br>
Another time grouped with a 52 mage. He used MS II, I used GV: Air. His pet got hit most of the time. Then we added another 60 mage, who got his epic pet out. Now it was MY pet that got hit all of the time, while the other two pets were left alone (quite frustrating).<br>
<br>
Btw. in each case I could sit next to the mob (once pets got aggro) and would not get any attention from the mob, I could also hit em with my stein (or try to) and they never turned on me.<br>
<br>
