<br>
   Perhaps a bit more help in determining agro for pets/warders.<br>
<br>
   From my observation, the second pet/warder to engage will gain the most agro.   For example, I was recently in DSP playing with the Hoppers.  I notice a 52 Magre LFG and invite him to duo.<br>
<br>
   I would pull with drowsy and listless the mob as it got near the camp.   Just after, I listless the mob, the Mage would send his elemental in, while I was still outside melee range.  Initially, his elemental would take a beating or the mob would continue after me, with his elemental hitting it from behind.<br>
<br>
   If the mob stopped and engaged the elemental, I would send my warder in, who would immediately gain almost all the agro.  After about 10 - 15 seconds, I could step into melee range without taking a hit<br>
<br>
   If the mob continued after me, my warder would engage on it's own at which point I would tank for a few seconds before stepping back.   When I would step back, the Elemental would take the agro instead of my warder.  After about 10 - 15 seconds, I would step back into melee range and take around 1/3rd of the agro.<br>
<br>
   At the time, I was 52, with my 49 warder.  My warder was level 39 and fully buffed.  The buffs he was recieving were;<br>
Raging Strength: +26 STR<br>
Spirit Of Monkey: +20 DEX<br>
Health: +31 STA<br>
Spiritual Brawn: +10 ATK +75 HP<br>
Protect: +14 AC<br>
Spirit Of Wind (Proc Buff): 112 DD(Plus Stun) +75 DEX<br>
Yekan's Quickeing (Haste Buff): 60% Haste +45 STR +20 ATK +12 AC<br>
Spirit Of Wolf(Movement Buff)<br>
<br>
   The Mage was using their earth pet, I am assuming Greater Conjuration Earth.   IIRC the GCE is level 42 or 43 and was fully buffed.  Not sure what buffs he put on, but I put on;<br>
Raging Strength: +26 STR<br>
Spirit Of Monkey: +20 DEX<br>
Health: +31 STA<br>
Spiritual Brawn: +10 ATK +75 HP<br>
Protect: +14 AC<br>
Spirit Of Wolf(Movement Buff)<br>
<br>
   Now to muddy the water a bit more, I should point out that I performed some tests a while back regarding Beastlord warders and /pet attack.  At the time, it appeared that Beastlord warders didn't attribute all their agro to the Beastlord, unless the Beastlord did a /pet attack.   This may help explain part of the scenario I was seeing when the mob would continue after me instead of stopping at the elemental.<br>
