<br>
<br>
The thing about level/ac aggro on pets doesn't appear to be true anymore.<br>
<br>
I had a Rak Ashir fight last night where we used 3 GC Fires. I had my 2 Box cleric there and sent in the Hammer pet after 10 seconds and the Hammer lives the WHOLE fight. (Although it ate one riposte and was knocked to 15% health on that one hit, he still survived.)<br>
<br>
The hammer/sword pets got a huge upgrade in offensive power, they double hit for 73's and are IMMUNE to AoE's and Spells. This makes them really valuable in AoE fights like Rak.<br>
<br>
Second note:<br>
Once a Necro gets the Spectre pets (Level 59, 61, 63 and 65 pets.) their attack range becomes HUGE and they use those scythes from father back than most pets. Nice thing.<br>
