<br>
WHo gets aggro first remains high on hate list.<br>
<br>
Who has best damage/delay ratio compared to their level gets high aggro (this is why monks, pets, rogues and twinks get high aggro)<br>
<br>
Procs add aggro (epic pet has ballistic aggro due to low lvl, extremely good ratio and procs)<br>
<br>
Who does most damage per hit gets high aggro (why 2handers now draw aggro good)<br>
<br>
Who is in closest proximity has high aggro (which is why NO ONE should be closer to an uber mob than the main tank, and why pets used to be able to hold aggro by pulling mobs inside thier mass)<br>
<br>
Spells seem to have individually coded aggro, slow, tash etc show this, Firebolt of Tallon is NUTSOID aggro and shoudltn be used on raid targets. You can chain cast 1k nukes and be fine, but FoT will get you wasted.<br>
